research_municipality_step.notes: Howell Township, NJ operates under a council-manager form of government, with a directly elected Mayor and a four-member Township Council elected at-large. The 'mayor_council' government type was chosen as the closest available option. Term expiration dates for Mayor Leggio (December 31, 2028), Councilwoman Fischer (December 31, 2026), Councilman Nadel (December 31, 2026), and Councilwoman O'Donnell (December 31, 2028) were found. The term expiration date for Councilman Michael Wrubel was not explicitly stated in the provided search results, but he is listed as a current council member on the official township website.
